Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.16,0:00:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, by saying yes, we got snow today,\Ndidn't we?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:04.48,0:00:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We collapsed the wave function, folks.\NLife is just collapsing the wave
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.96,0:00:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,function all the time, isn't it?\NWell, we never did get around to what
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.84,0:00:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the subject was for today. for today.\NPeople uh it's always comical to me you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.96,0:00:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,know uh people say what is the subject\Ngoing to be
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.64,0:00:42.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the subject is going to be whatever\Nis spoken
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.32,0:00:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,and I don't know what the subject spoken\Nis until I hear it so how would I know
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.71,0:00:53.84,Default,,0,0,0,,like saying to uh\NPaul McCartney, what song are you going
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.84,0:01:00.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to write next week? Well, I don't know.\NAnyway, today was supposed to be about
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.39,0:01:06.72,Default,,0,0,0,,what I call the zen of daily life.\NUm,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.72,0:01:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,spirituality and everyday life. Okay.\NSo, now I know what the subject is,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.11,0:01:15.84,Default,,0,0,0,,folks. And\Nwe did talk about the zen of chicken
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.84,0:01:21.36,Default,,0,0,0,,coop, didn't we? where intention, the\Npower of intention and of course in
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.36,0:01:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual work the power of intention is\Nthe driving laser beam that carries you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.75,0:01:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,through to your destination. Huh?\NSomebody asked me about peace, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.96,0:01:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh you know, I was joking when I\Nsaid, you know, peace and war, they're
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.20,0:01:44.24,Default,,0,0,0,,all the same to me. Um\Nso that people wouldn't think I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.24,0:01:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,serious, but frankly, they are the same\Nto me.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.28,0:01:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,because one can be in in a state of\Ninfinite peace right in the middle of
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.88,0:01:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,war and feel a profound state of peace\Nas you walk right into physical death.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.28,0:02:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh and that's because of the power of\None's alignment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.56,0:02:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't join any campaigns for peace.\NThe reason is you cannot create peace
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.59,0:02:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,any like enlightenment. You see you\Ncan't create enlightenment. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.59,0:02:23.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't create peace.\NIt's the state when that which opposes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.59,0:02:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it is removed. Then it spontaneously\Nstands there because it is there all the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.23,0:02:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,time.\NYou cannot create peace. So a parade for
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.95,0:02:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,peace may be entertaining\Nbut what we did this morning probably
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.20,0:02:40.80,Default,,0,0,0,,had more profound effect on the\Nlikelihood the potentiality of peace
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.80,0:02:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,than a parade, you know.\NYou cannot create peace because it is a
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.95,0:02:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,quality of divinity which stands forth\Nwhen you remove that which is obscuring
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.72,0:03:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,it.\NWhen you remove the clouds, the sun
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.56,0:03:06.15,Default,,0,0,0,,shines forth, but that does not cause\Nthe sun to shine.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:06.15,0:03:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You remove the clouds and the sun shines\Nforth because it is there. So
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.31,0:03:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,what we're going to do is remove\Nthe foundations out of which the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.04,0:03:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,eventuality of war becomes\Nu a necessity by virtue of how it's been
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.48,0:03:35.59,Default,,0,0,0,,set up to happen.\NThe underpinnings then are falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.59,0:03:40.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently,\Nit is only by virtue of the stacking of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.23,0:03:44.48,Default,,0,0,0,,one falsehood upon another that war\Nensues.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.48,0:03:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Consequently, the identification of that\Nwhich is false from that which is true
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.20,0:04:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,does more to service peace than anything\Nelse you can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.15,0:04:06.08,Default,,0,0,0,,to remove the sheep's clothing from the\Nwolf and reveal the wolf
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.08,0:04:14.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is what Jesus Christ said is the way to\Npeace.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.48,0:04:19.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason to understand the ego and how\Nits structure arises out of the animal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.75,0:04:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,kingdom.\NAnd because of survival, the animal must
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.04,0:04:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,of necessity be into mechanical duality.\NWhen he goes to eat a rabbit, he has to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.19,0:04:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,know where the rabbit is.\NI'm here. The rabbit's there. He also
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.12,0:04:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,classifies things dualistically, edible\Nand noted edible. A stone is not edible.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.60,0:04:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And a rabbit is\Nso that intrinsic mechanism then
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.63,0:04:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,conditions uh the mind to a dualistic\Nto a dualistic way of perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.56,0:05:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's the difficulty of spiritual\Nwork to transcend that propensity to
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.60,0:05:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,duality.\NAnd the underpinning in the modern human
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.19,0:05:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,psyche is in that principle of\Ncausality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.96,0:05:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why with every lecture we say\Nnothing is causing anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.68,0:05:25.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is spontaneously becoming its\Nown potentiality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.44,0:05:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And that likelihood then is made\Npossible by saying yes and collapsing
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.03,0:05:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the way wave function so that it can\Nbecome an actuality.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.03,0:05:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Other than that it's a potentiality but\Nwhen you say yes to it it becomes an
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.75,0:05:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,actuality. Huh?\NWe're supposed to be talking about
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.08,0:05:59.12,Default,,0,0,0,,personal life.\NFor many people it means relationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.12,0:06:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Personal life centers around\Nrelationship. And what makes
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.80,0:06:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,relationship work?\NAny bookstore is full of 150 books on
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.24,0:06:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how to make your relationship work,\Nfolks.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.68,0:06:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you knew, you wouldn't be reading\Nit, would you? So
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.00,0:06:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,if he knew, he wouldn't be reading it.\NAnyway,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.68,0:06:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,um what it has to do with what the world\Nfools around with is involvement.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.44,0:06:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Couples are involved with each other.\NBoy, are they involved, but they're not
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.08,0:06:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,aligned. So, the secret of\Nwhat makes a relationship work
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.84,0:06:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,effortlessly\Nis
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.60,0:06:48.63,Default,,0,0,0,,alignment. The two people are aligned\Nwith each other in purpose and intent.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.63,0:06:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Now because the mind thinks in terms of\Npriorities
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.72,0:06:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,what you choose as your priority now\Nwill organize everything underneath of
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.36,0:07:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,it. See\Nto win the argument is not really your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.84,0:07:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,priority if you're aligned with the\Nrelationship because your alignment is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.52,0:07:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,with the workability of the relationship\Nrather than the egotistical
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,pleasure of being right.\Nthe solar plex. Most couples get
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.56,0:07:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,involved in a solar plexus power\Nstruggle over control and who's right
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.36,0:07:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and who's wrong and they get into a game\Nof oneupmanship.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.47,0:07:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,So any relationship not just marital but\Nwith children with the world with one's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.63,0:07:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,country then has to do with alignment.\NA couple who are aligned with each other
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.12,0:08:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,means that their well-being\Nis primary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.24,0:08:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,whether her coffee is ready in the\Nmorning becomes more important
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.84,0:08:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,than going to the bathroom right away.\NYou can wait and get her coffee going
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.59,0:08:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and then you go to the bathroom. You\Nknow this thing
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.80,0:08:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the choice every morning.\NShe wakes at 6:00. It's quarter 6. I got
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.75,0:08:28.16,Default,,0,0,0,,time to go to the bathroom. So the\Nalignment with the other person's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.16,0:08:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness. Why? Because that's your joy.\NThat's the source of your joy. The
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.71,0:08:35.91,Default,,0,0,0,,source of joy is not winning an\Nargument. You don't feel joyful after
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.91,0:08:41.36,Default,,0,0,0,,you win an argument. You usually feel\Nguilty or you're still poed or I should
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.36,0:08:47.51,Default,,0,0,0,,have said that or I could have won if\NI'd only said so. So
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.51,0:08:52.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the a a relationship based on\Nwinningness, who's got control, who's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:56.72,Default,,0,0,0,,got the power,\Nuh
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.72,0:09:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,is not going to be gratifying\Nbecause they both have an economic stake
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.20,0:09:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and etc. Many of these dismal\Nrelationships can, you know, survive
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.04,0:09:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,over time.\NFor the relationship to be gratifying,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.76,0:09:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you're both aligned. You're aligned with\Nintentionality.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.92,0:09:23.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Where is intentionality again? So\Nintentionality then becomes your the
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.83,0:09:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,priority is the alignment of your\Nrelationship.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.56,0:09:35.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You're devoted you're devoted to\Nthe lovingness of the relationship. You
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.20,0:09:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,devoted to be of service to the other\Nto their needs and their happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.68,0:09:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That is their joy.\NThe purpose of the relationship then is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.88,0:09:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,joy.\NThe purpose of the alignment with God
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.16,0:10:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,with devotion\Nis one of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.16,0:10:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't mean an argument won't arise.\NThe argument is usually one of speed.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.92,0:10:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,It's you'll find out you're both people\Nare too speeded up in their expectations
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.20,0:10:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,and they both head for the refrigerator\Nat the same time and bump into each
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.64,0:10:31.20,Default,,0,0,0,,other.\NUm but that doesn't change people who
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.20,0:10:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,are aligned. People who are aligned\Nthough that bounces off of them. They
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.24,0:10:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,realize they were in a hurry. So we get\Nspeeded up in the world. We have
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple tasks we're trying to\Naccomplish by a certain specified time.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.88,0:10:49.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Lunch today is going to be at 12. You\Nknow what I mean? That we've got this
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.83,0:10:54.32,Default,,0,0,0,,pressure on us. Everything's got to be\Nsaid by 12. You understand?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.32,0:10:58.16,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to be back by 1. You know what I\Nmean? The bus leaves at 3:30. So, we're
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.16,0:11:03.27,Default,,0,0,0,,all under this particular kind of a\Npressure in our society. This is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.27,0:11:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,cultural, by the way. Cultural.\NThere are many societies in which time
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.32,0:11:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,does not become a dominant part of the\Nego. The sense of time is a programming
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.00,0:11:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,superimposed on\Ntransitory perception. It's superimposed
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.39,0:11:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,by the ego. It's like a time track which\Nthe ego superimposes.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.07,0:11:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And once you get out of that time track,\Nthe relief is tremendous. When you're no
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.48,0:11:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,longer driven by time, it's fantastic.\NThere are cultures in which that is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.12,0:11:41.60,Default,,0,0,0,,endemic.\NI remember being in Ecuador probably the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.60,0:11:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,early 70s. It was uh tourists didn't go\Nto South America in those years much
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.92,0:11:48.95,Default,,0,0,0,,less Ecuador. Nobody ever heard of\NEcuador.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.95,0:11:55.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And um but the minute you're in Ecuador\Nat about 10,000 12,000 ft time stops.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.60,0:12:00.64,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just not sort of heavily energized\Nin their culture. Nobody ever says what
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.64,0:12:06.24,Default,,0,0,0,,time is it?\NThere was two planes out a week.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.24,0:12:13.68,Default,,0,0,0,,two planes a week out of Ecuador to the\NUS and uh they went to uh I forget where
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.68,0:12:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,they went. It's not important. Florida\Nsomeplace. Anyway, they're out of Keo,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.16,0:12:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,which is the capital of Ecuador. Uh so\Nin this never land of no timeness,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.48,0:12:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,uh I had to remember that the ticket\Nsaid we were leaving Wednesday.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.16,0:12:36.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we go to the airport at uh Wednesday\Nand uh this lady says, "The Wednesday
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.24,0:12:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,plane doesn't leave till Saturday." Oh,\Nif I was in Chicago, I'd be in a fit,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.72,0:12:49.20,Default,,0,0,0,,wouldn't you? I want my tickets\Nrefunded. I'm calling my congressman,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.20,0:12:56.39,Default,,0,0,0,,emailing O'Reilly.\NDidn't even Didn't Oh, so what? Just
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.39,0:12:59.44,Default,,0,0,0,,didn't give a damn. Oh, the Wednesday\Nplane doesn't leave till Saturday. No,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.44,0:13:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,not till Saturday. Oh, okay. It leaves a\NSaturday at noon. Oh, okay. Fine. Oh,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.48,0:13:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,okay. Back to the It didn't make any\Ndifference at all. Go back there at at
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.80,0:13:14.16,Default,,0,0,0,,noon. In the middle of the airport in\NKeo, there's a big uh old clock. What's
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.16,0:13:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it from the 1920s or something? Anyway,\Nit stopped years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.76,0:13:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody had fixed a clock in years. It\Njust was stopped at some something. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.76,0:13:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,the Wednesday plane didn't leave till\NSaturday and the clock stopped. And so,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.72,0:13:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, being an American, I get\Nthere, you know, 11:15 or something like
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.92,0:13:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that to catch the 12:00 plane and\Nwaiting for the plane. There's only one
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.92,0:13:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,plane on the runway. As I say, there's\Nonly two planes a week. So, here's this
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.12,0:13:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,um plane sitting on the runway and the\Nengines are running, you know, and so I
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.72,0:13:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,expect the quarter 12 we're going to\Nboard or something. Quarter 12, all of a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.63,0:13:56.24,Default,,0,0,0,,sudden the plane's engine stopped.\NI said to the the lady there at the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.24,0:13:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,desk, there was one lady at the desk in\Nthe airport. I said, "What is it?" She
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.60,0:14:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,says, "It's it'sa time.\NThey're not going to start the plane at
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.32,0:14:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,quarter to 12 and siesta is at 12." So\Nthe plane shut down from 12:00 to 3.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.32,0:14:20.32,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm thinking to myself in my American\Nmind, think of what the overhead, just
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.32,0:14:25.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the insurance, the maintenance, the the\Nthe infrastructure to keep this stupid
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.36,0:14:30.07,Default,,0,0,0,,plane sitting there for for 3 hours\Nwhile they wait for the siesta time.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.07,0:14:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the Wednesday plane didn't leave\Nat Saturday. It didn't leave at 12:00.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.04,0:14:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,We didn't pull off till 3:00 and they\Nforgot the baggage anyway. It was
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.56,0:14:40.24,Default,,0,0,0,,running.\NIt ran down to Chile and had to come
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.24,0:14:44.72,Default,,0,0,0,,home a couple days later. I don't know.\NAnd and you see it just didn't matter.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.72,0:14:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't matter. It was irrelevant.\NTotally irrelevant. So, you know, we
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.36,0:14:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,take on that time pressure so endemic in\Nour culture. Our culture calibrates, you
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.63,0:15:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,know, around 430 or something and uh\Neverything runs by the clock. So,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.76,0:15:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I just wanted to point out that that\Nit's not um an imprinted reality in your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.48,0:15:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,brain. It's very cultural. And all of\Nyou know that there are experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.32,0:15:16.95,Default,,0,0,0,,which take you out of time and there's\Nno way of knowing what really what time
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.95,0:15:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,it is. So you stop clocking things in\Nterms of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.16,0:15:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So the alignment of a relationship then\Nis somewhat of that nature
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.12,0:15:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in which the time part is not period.\Nyour tasks are caught in time and
