Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.07,0:46:17.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether love is better than hate.\NThe most primitive axioms have not even
Dialogue: 0,0:46:17.68,0:46:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,been agreed upon.\NWhat is the value of human life? You
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.48,0:46:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,think you know, you don't know. Another\Nc culture thinks you're idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.56,0:46:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Break the law, execution.\NThat's the law of the land. They have a
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.80,0:46:38.16,Default,,0,0,0,,drug problem, of course not. But you get\Ncaught with drugs, you're executed.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:38.16,0:46:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They think that's the correct way.\NWho's to say it's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:43.92,0:46:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,They don't have a drug problem there.\NSingapore, I think, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:53.52,0:46:59.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Drugs, death, instant execution.\NThey think that's what makes sense and
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.83,0:47:04.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our way is stupid. You know what I'm\Nsaying? How can we sell our way to a
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.24,0:47:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,people who see it differently? So you\Nsee we're dealing in difference of
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.48,0:47:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,paradigms of the real versus the unreal,\Nthe important versus the unimportant. It
Dialogue: 0,0:47:13.20,0:47:16.40,Default,,0,0,0,,has to do with content and context. It\Nhas to do with where you are in the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:16.40,0:47:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution of consciousness. It has to do\Nwhere you are with the evolution of your
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.96,0:47:26.64,Default,,0,0,0,,culture. As I mentioned before, when the\Npresident of China was interviewed by an
Dialogue: 0,0:47:26.64,0:47:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,American\Ninterviewer on TV, I was embarrassed for
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.35,0:47:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,America to tell you embarrassed. The\Ndisrespect of this
Dialogue: 0,0:47:37.04,0:47:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,uh cocky guy against the ruler of the\Ngreatest nation on earth, China is the
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.72,0:47:48.07,Default,,0,0,0,,greatest nation on earth. Who do you\Nthink he was talking to? That man is
Dialogue: 0,0:47:48.07,0:47:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely brilliant. got an IQ that outf\Nfox the interviewer. It's embarrassing
Dialogue: 0,0:47:54.07,0:48:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that lack of humility, you see. Um\Nbecause our cultural style doesn't work
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.31,0:48:05.11,Default,,0,0,0,,for for them and and vice versa. So he\Nsaid, "Well, we may have some civil
Dialogue: 0,0:48:05.11,0:48:10.56,Default,,0,0,0,,rights violations in your viewpoint, but\Nwhat about the drugs, the crime, the
Dialogue: 0,0:48:10.56,0:48:15.11,Default,,0,0,0,,wars?\NUh
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.11,0:48:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,we have 3% of our population in prison\Nright now, the highest in the world."
Dialogue: 0,0:48:18.96,0:48:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, so he looked back at him. He\Nsaid, "You do have a few problems of
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.44,0:48:27.59,Default,,0,0,0,,your own." I thought it was sort of a\Nsubtle way to put him back down again.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.59,0:48:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,But you see how arrogance then polarizes\Nthe world. Arrogance is what polariz
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.80,0:48:37.11,Default,,0,0,0,,polarizes world. They don't hate us\Nbecause we're successful. They hate us
Dialogue: 0,0:48:37.11,0:48:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because we rub their face in it. That's\Nwhy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.35,0:48:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Um,\Nso what we need then is to pull in our
Dialogue: 0,0:48:46.88,0:48:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,pseudopodia from everybody else's\Nbusiness. Try humility. Try supporting
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.76,0:48:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,peace and peace is not supported by our\Nwe're right and your own.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.68,0:49:01.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're just talking about a domestic\Nissue now because we're the human family
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.59,0:49:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,is just one huge huge family. So if\Nwe're aligned with the freedom of other
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.92,0:49:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,people to be who they are then\Nu and stop um bullying them uh with
Dialogue: 0,0:49:13.52,0:49:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,moral superiority\Nuh and the dogooderism
Dialogue: 0,0:49:18.55,0:49:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of people who want to restrict the\Nfreedom of others so that their pet
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.88,0:49:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalities can be forced on others.\NSo that's what prevails in all
Dialogue: 0,0:49:28.31,0:49:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,relationships in the domestic. It\Ncertainly makes the difference between
Dialogue: 0,0:49:32.55,0:49:37.59,Default,,0,0,0,,joy and a feeling of fulfillment. So a\Nsuccessful relationship then is one that
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.59,0:49:42.55,Default,,0,0,0,,brings joy, contentment, a feeling of\Nsecurity.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.55,0:49:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,If the relationship is working, you feel\Nemotionally safe with the other person.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:47.83,0:49:52.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Emotionally safe. What does that mean?\NIt means you can reveal your downside
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.55,0:49:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other person will help you\Novercome it. Reontextualize it for us.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.52,0:50:01.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So one of the greatest gifts we give\Neach other is we recontextualize it back
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.20,0:50:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,to the other person\Ninstead of grieving over that la loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:06.48,0:50:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't you see that that which you were\Nattached to is tying you down and now
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.16,0:50:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,without that in your life your life is\Nfreer. It's true when you lose one job
Dialogue: 0,0:50:15.68,0:50:19.76,Default,,0,0,0,,you now have the freedom to choose all\Nover again. It's not just loss it's gain
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.76,0:50:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,of freedom to totally reassess your\Nposition your vocational choice. Do you
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.88,0:50:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,really want to stay here anymore? you\Nreally want to work that are those the
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.92,0:50:33.44,Default,,0,0,0,,work goals you really have is salary the\Nonly thing that counts is the pleasantry
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.44,0:50:37.68,Default,,0,0,0,,of the people you how important is it\Nyou know the girls ranch arm chief of
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.68,0:50:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,staff you know the main attraction is\Nfirst of all my services are needed and
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.64,0:50:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a shortage of doctors but the\Nother thing is the staff is joyful to be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.92,0:50:51.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with and as chief of staff that's been\Nmy purpose to have a joyful staff to be
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.35,0:50:55.35,Default,,0,0,0,,with in which we do everything out of\Ncooperation and love and mutual respect
Dialogue: 0,0:50:55.35,0:50:58.72,Default,,0,0,0,,so You naturally want to stay there\Nbecause it's, you know, wonderful place.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.72,0:51:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,What they pay is sort of irrelevant, you\Nknow. Um, it's secondary. It's the
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.35,0:51:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,feeling of satisfaction that you get out\Nof that particular workplace. So, you
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.80,0:51:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,lose a job, you say instead of grieving\Na loss, this is maybe a call to
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.35,0:51:18.16,Default,,0,0,0,,reexamine what are my goals in life?\NHuh? What are my goals in life? What
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.16,0:51:22.00,Default,,0,0,0,,really makes me happy? What makes me\Nfeel satisfied? And there's a certain
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.00,0:51:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,point in which making money is very,\Nvery important. And you should
Dialogue: 0,0:51:26.07,0:51:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It should be committed to that because\Nit is necessary to the achievement of
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.55,0:51:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,certain goals. So it becomes subsidiary.\NIt's not the money. It's the fact that
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.44,0:51:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you know you can afford health insurance\Nand that has to do with your wife's
Dialogue: 0,0:51:39.20,0:51:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,security and happiness and the safety\Nand security of your family. So all this
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.88,0:51:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you see again subserves love. It's\Nbecause of lovingness that you want
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.44,0:51:53.11,Default,,0,0,0,,those around you to be and to feel safe\Nand cared for and loved. And um that's
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.11,0:51:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,why the bread earner earns the bread is\Nfor the joy and peace and happiness
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.28,0:52:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,security of the family and those that\Nthey love. So one's alignment with love,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.76,0:52:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,one's alignment with integrity.\NSo recontextualization then is one of
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.20,0:52:13.52,Default,,0,0,0,,the greatest ways we can serve each\Nother. And uh if one of them one is down
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.52,0:52:21.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the dumps, the other one says\Nbut what about and presents it. So
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.44,0:52:26.24,Default,,0,0,0,,it's our love for each other that brings\Nus about peace. Our love for
Dialogue: 0,0:52:26.24,0:52:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,each other and our love for our own\Nexistence. You see, because you cannot
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.28,0:52:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,love God and hate your own existence.\NUnless you glory in your own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.35,0:52:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you cannot glory in the presence of God.\NBecause the evidence of God is the
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.64,0:52:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective awareness of your own\Nexistence and that is the source of joy.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:52.31,0:52:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And so out of your love for each other\Nand your alignment in the relationship,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:56.48,0:53:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you experience the joy of your own\Nexistence just as I enjoy being what I
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.48,0:54:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,am to thee this day.\NWe'll reconvene at 1:00. God bless.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.00,0:54:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Fore! Foreign! Foreign!\Nforeign
Dialogue: 0,0:54:30.00,0:56:45.44,Default,,0,0,0,,go\NGoing
Dialogue: 0,0:56:45.44,0:57:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Fore\Nfor we hope and Rick
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.16,0:57:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Going\Nto go rainbow.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.28,0:58:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Womanch.\Nforeign.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.20,0:59:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,No\Nmore
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.64,0:59:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,in no\Nglor.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:26.88,0:59:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you. Let's\Ndo an
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.72,0:59:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,uh in the interest of equality we will\Ndoctor and I would like to do an oh
Dialogue: 0,0:59:41.68,0:59:48.31,Default,,0,0,0,,could you uh actually all of us could\Nyou uh put that up the oh that was just
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.31,0:59:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,on\Njust
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.64,1:00:04.31,Default,,0,0,0,,it's yeah it's on that CDA\NThe second track
Dialogue: 0,1:00:04.31,1:00:21.04,Default,,0,0,0,,you can join with us. Find it yourself.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:21.04,1:00:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:47.76,1:01:25.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.\NOh.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:25.76,1:01:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,If that don't make God happy, nothing\Nwill.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.79,1:01:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I can hear him laughing as we speak. He\Nhe talks it only in Sanskrit.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.28,1:01:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Nico. You're a great gift to\Nus.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.35,1:01:56.16,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Well, I thought we might enjoy that. So,\Nanybody have any questions about it?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.16,1:02:00.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Questions arise in content but in\Ncontext there are no questions because
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.55,1:02:06.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it's belong beyond languaging.\NIt's the subjective experience of one's
Dialogue: 0,1:02:06.48,1:02:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,existence. Yeah.\NAnd that's the radical reality of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:13.76,1:02:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,subjective the subjective state.\NThe sense of eye is the radical state of
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.28,1:02:25.92,Default,,0,0,0,,subjectivity.\NWhen one lets go identification with the
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.92,1:02:34.79,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality, the mind, the emotions,\Nyeah, and all definitions of self,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:34.79,1:02:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,that which prevails constantly in all\Ntimes, in all places,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.44,1:02:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,is why it's difficult to\Nbecome aware of. It's like space. We
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.44,1:02:52.31,Default,,0,0,0,,take it for granted. It's the sense of\Nself, the sense of one's existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.31,1:02:56.31,Default,,0,0,0,,People\Nsay what is the fastest way to that
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.31,1:03:02.64,Default,,0,0,0,,space? The fastest way to that space is\Nto witness to notice
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.64,1:03:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,that the mind at all times is silent\Nexcept for a small talkingness space
Dialogue: 0,1:03:10.31,1:03:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody focuses on the talkingness\Nspace because that's where the action
Dialogue: 0,1:03:15.03,1:03:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,is. That's where the entertainment is.\NSo, there's a little TV set in your head
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.72,1:03:30.55,Default,,0,0,0,,that keeps you fascinated and hypnotized\Nbecause it talks all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.55,1:03:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What you don't realize is that the\Nmajority of your mind is silent at all
Dialogue: 0,1:03:35.52,1:03:42.16,Default,,0,0,0,,times.\NRight this instant,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:42.16,1:03:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,99.9%\Nof your mind is silent.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:46.64,1:03:54.72,Default,,0,0,0,,1% is tracking what's happening.\NA tenth of 1% is tracking what's being
Dialogue: 0,1:03:54.72,1:04:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,said.\NThe prevailing silence of the mind is
Dialogue: 0,1:04:01.68,1:04:11.03,Default,,0,0,0,,the source, the space, the presence, the\Nawareness
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.03,1:04:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,of the reality of that which you are.\NThe reality of that which you are then
Dialogue: 0,1:04:17.03,1:04:24.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is in the area of the silence.\NSo there's no point of looking for it in
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.64,1:04:28.31,Default,,0,0,0,,reading another book because it's not in\Nthe book.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.31,1:04:34.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not in the construct.\NWhat the instruction does is show you
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.96,1:04:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,how to leave\Nthe that dimension of distraction and
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.68,1:04:49.03,Default,,0,0,0,,retreat into the inner reality.\NThat's the purpose
Dialogue: 0,1:04:49.03,1:04:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,which in which mind serves no mind.\NAnd therefore the only purpose of
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.11,1:05:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,the mind is to lead you to\Nwhere no mind is.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.40,1:05:15.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. No mind. Where is no mind? Good\NGod.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:15.68,1:05:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No mind is taking care of everything\Ntoday. So we don't have to worry about
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.11,1:05:24.72,Default,,0,0,0,,anything because no mind is guaranteed\Nthat it'll snow today.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.72,1:05:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and that Nico will do the chant and that\Nall will be well and that lunch will be
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.16,1:05:35.92,Default,,0,0,0,,served\Nand that is all taken care of silently
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.92,1:05:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the options because of the\Nthings we have said yes to then
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.79,1:05:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the potentiality becomes an actuality\Nto have chosen enlightenment as one's
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.11,1:05:55.76,Default,,0,0,0,,goal is the only reason anyone is here\Nso by reason of choice or a reason of
Dialogue: 0,1:05:55.76,1:06:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,saying yes one manifests into one's life\Nthe way
Dialogue: 0,1:06:01.92,1:06:07.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and uh the company of people that are on\Na similar way uh who mutually support
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.52,1:06:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,each other because they're aligned with\Nthe same goal.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:23.35,1:06:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The field of consciousness then is a\Nfield of infinite power. Infinite power,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.00,1:06:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,stationary, unmoving\Nby choice. What we do is we allow the
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.35,1:06:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,infinite power\Nto take us effortlessly to where we're
Dialogue: 0,1:06:44.31,1:06:48.16,Default,,0,0,0,,going.\NTherefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:48.16,1:06:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,although intention is absolute, effort\Nis really minimal.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:56.48,1:07:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The only effort is then letting go of\Nthe satisfaction out of the
Dialogue: 0,1:07:02.00,1:07:07.92,Default,,0,0,0,,positionality\Nwhich is blocking it.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.92,1:07:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As we let go the satisfaction,\Nwhat we're getting out of being right or
Dialogue: 0,1:07:13.20,1:07:20.24,Default,,0,0,0,,winning, whatever it might be, you will\Nyou don't have to let go of being right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.24,1:07:25.83,Default,,0,0,0,,You only have to get let go of the\Nsatisfaction of it. So the attachments
Dialogue: 0,1:07:25.83,1:07:31.35,Default,,0,0,0,,that we talk about how to let go of\Nattachments, attachments to what? The
Dialogue: 0,1:07:31.35,1:07:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment is not to winning. The\Nattachment is to the satisfaction.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:37.20,1:07:44.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The attachment is to the satisfaction\Nof burying the dagger deep in the heart
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.31,1:07:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,of our enemy. How gratifying.\NEarn
Dialogue: 0,1:07:52.16,1:07:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,make him suffer for what he's done to\Nus.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.28,1:08:02.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what we're attached to. The\Npleasure of that. Okay. We're not
Dialogue: 0,1:08:02.31,1:08:07.11,Default,,0,0,0,,attached to turning daggers in people's\Nhearts. I mean, it's a drag.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.11,1:08:11.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Get blood all over you. The guy screams.\NI mean, Jesus, that
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.68,1:08:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,not exactly pleasant. No, what you're\Nyou want is the gratification.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.35,1:08:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, when you see that the ego is really\Neasy to transcend by letting go,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.75,1:08:29.27,Default,,0,0,0,,the gratifications we get out of its\Ntemptations. So, what is temptation?
Dialogue: 0,1:08:29.27,1:08:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Temptation then is the attachment to the\Ngratification of the ego's positions.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.52,1:08:39.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That's all.\NThe shorter way is to let go of
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.75,1:08:43.75,Default,,0,0,0,,attachment itself.\NAnd therefore, I'll give you a secret
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.75,1:08:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,how to get enlightened before dinner\Ntime.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:51.44,1:08:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Attachment itself is the attachment.\NThe Buddha Sarin
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.35,1:09:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the senses. No, it's the attachment\Nto the senses. It's not sex and money
Dialogue: 0,1:09:03.60,1:09:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and fame and power and all those things.\NIt's the attachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.31,1:09:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,All right? So, curiously, the mind is\Nattached to attachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.88,1:09:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you see what we look for is a common\Nroot that we can cut that root and then
Dialogue: 0,1:09:22.56,1:09:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,a hole.\Nimmense dimension of the ego collapses.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.92,1:09:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We're attached to attachment itself.\NWhy so? Well, certainly in the process
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.27,1:09:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of evolution,\Nattachment is how physical survival
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.60,1:09:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,comes about. One is attached to the\Numbilical accord, attached to the
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.88,1:09:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,placenta, attached to mother's womb.\NOutside the womb, then one is attached
Dialogue: 0,1:09:48.15,1:09:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to the mother, the mother's milk, the\Nmother's nurturance, etc. Attachment
Dialogue: 0,1:09:53.44,1:10:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes what we're attached to.\NWe're attached to attachment.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:01.28,1:10:07.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the sophisticated child,\Nthe more evolved child, because we're
Dialogue: 0,1:10:07.67,1:10:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,all born with a certain level of\Nconsciousness,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:10.71,1:10:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes attached to the love, the love\Nof the mother. The less evolved being
Dialogue: 0,1:10:16.48,1:10:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,gets attached to the physicality of the\Nmother
Dialogue: 0,1:10:20.71,1:10:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is unable to discern. It's not the\Nmother that's keeping you alive. It's
Dialogue: 0,1:10:26.00,1:10:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the mother's love. To ascribe one's\Nsurvival then to the linear is the great
Dialogue: 0,1:10:32.88,1:10:38.08,Default,,0,0,0,,error because your survival is coming\Nfrom the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.08,1:10:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,In World War II, the children, the\Ninfants were taken out of London, the
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.84,1:10:46.48,Default,,0,0,0,,time of the Blitz, and they were taken\Nout into
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.48,1:10:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,doiciles out in the safe country and\Nthey died by the thousands. They stopped
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.60,1:10:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,eating, they became apathetic, they\Nbecame arasmic, they became depressed,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.40,1:11:04.15,Default,,0,0,0,,they stopped responding and they died. H\Nthey died.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.15,1:11:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nphysicality then is not enough. It buff
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.19,1:11:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,it baffles science because nutritionally\Nthey had everything vitamins and
Dialogue: 0,1:11:13.36,1:11:20.96,Default,,0,0,0,,balanced diets and germfree environments\Netc. And they died right and left. And
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.96,1:11:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,then they brought in some nannies.\NWhat's the matter with these infants?
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.88,1:11:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And the nannies began to hug them and\Ncuddle them and jostle them on their
Dialogue: 0,1:11:28.15,1:11:35.28,Default,,0,0,0,,knee and box them on their ears when\Nthey deserved it and they flourished.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:35.28,1:11:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So\Nsurvival comes from the nonlinear.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:39.60,1:11:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,If you came from the linear, those\Nchildren would have thrived.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.15,1:11:48.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Scientifically designed nutritional\Ndiets.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:48.56,1:11:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Good medical care, safe doicile,\Nand they died by the thousands.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:58.15,1:12:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,a dirty, horrible old nanny with germs\Nall over,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:02.40,1:12:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,jouncing them around and doing all kinds\Nof unhygienic things and the child
Dialogue: 0,1:12:06.56,1:12:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,prospers.\NAll right? So, one's survival then is
Dialogue: 0,1:12:14.64,1:12:19.84,Default,,0,0,0,,coming from the nonlinear.\NAttachment is the mistake of attaching
Dialogue: 0,1:12:19.84,1:12:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it to the linear.\NTo attach your survival to the linear.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:24.88,1:12:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,To think that it's the ego that's\Nkeeping you alive is making the mistake
Dialogue: 0,1:12:29.44,1:12:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,of the child\Nwho gets attached to the physicality and
Dialogue: 0,1:12:34.64,1:12:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,fails to get that is the energy field of\Nthe the love of the mother to which it
Dialogue: 0,1:12:40.40,1:12:46.32,Default,,0,0,0,,owes its survival.\NOne's survival is guaranteed until the
Dialogue: 0,1:12:46.32,1:12:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,point of death.\NThe good news is
Dialogue: 0,1:12:56.80,1:13:01.60,Default,,0,0,0,,you came in with a certain calibrated\Nlevel of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.60,1:13:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The good news is you didn't enter the\Nembryo until the third month of the
Dialogue: 0,1:13:05.28,1:13:11.04,Default,,0,0,0,,embryo's life.\NThe good news is that the time of which
Dialogue: 0,1:13:11.04,1:13:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to leave the body has\Nalready set at the time of birth.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:18.00,1:13:26.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So I worry fine.\N>> Then we read of uh about 20 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:26.56,1:13:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the one I always liked was the\Nairliner at 30,000 ft and the door
Dialogue: 0,1:13:32.80,1:13:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,suddenly came off and exactly one person\Nwas picked out of the airliner. 300
Dialogue: 0,1:13:38.64,1:13:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,people. She happened to be the\Nstewardist. The stewardist was picked
Dialogue: 0,1:13:42.71,1:13:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,out.\NNo one else. Huh.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.15,1:13:51.84,Default,,0,0,0,,When is your time is your time. When\Nit's not, it's not. So why worry about
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.84,1:14:00.00,Default,,0,0,0,,it? You understand?\NIf you project yourself forward to the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.00,1:14:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,time of death, picture yourself laying\Non the deathbed, families gathered all
Dialogue: 0,1:14:05.19,1:14:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,around, doctor looks grave.\NI was going to say the hers is waiting
Dialogue: 0,1:14:12.88,1:14:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,outside, but that's not the room.\Nracing his engine.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.56,1:14:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, as you are there on death store,\NI want you to realize that to get to the
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.15,1:14:31.36,Default,,0,0,0,,your deathbed, you have to have\Nsurvived.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:31.36,1:14:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So when I say you have to survive all\Nthe way to your deathbed, you can quit
Dialogue: 0,1:14:35.12,1:14:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,worrying about it because somehow\Nsomething kept you alive and going until
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.48,1:14:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,that great moment. Okay? Great moment of\Nrelease.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:45.60,1:14:49.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't have to worry about life\Nand birth and death, that's solves a lot
Dialogue: 0,1:14:49.92,1:15:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of problems\Nto be attached to attachment itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.00,1:15:09.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, attachment itself is a\Nprocess. It thinks that clingingness is
Dialogue: 0,1:15:09.76,1:15:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,what guarantees your survival.\NSo the clean clingingness is to
Dialogue: 0,1:15:15.19,1:15:20.40,Default,,0,0,0,,cleanness itself.\NAnd in letting go of the cleanness
Dialogue: 0,1:15:20.40,1:15:25.84,Default,,0,0,0,,itself,\Nthere is nothing to which it can be
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.84,1:15:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,attached.\NThen you're free forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:34.15,1:15:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Free forever.\NThe physic the physicality is sometimes
Dialogue: 0,1:15:58.80,1:16:05.92,Default,,0,0,0,,uh in the way of\Nthe expression of ecstasy.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:05.92,1:16:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we listen to that music, you want\Nto play the music,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.00,1:16:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we said we calibrated that music around\N740.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:13.92,1:16:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,When I talk about calibrating things,\Nwe're talking generally about a range.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:19.92,1:16:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Um, I wanted to clarify that also\Nwhether a thing is 735 or 740 in the way
Dialogue: 0,1:16:27.36,1:16:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in which in the context in which we're\Nusing it is irrelevant. What you want to
Dialogue: 0,1:16:31.44,1:16:36.96,Default,,0,0,0,,know is it in the 700s, low 700s, high\N700s, is it over 500? Maybe there's a
Dialogue: 0,1:16:36.96,1:16:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,critical line of 200 or 500. But in\Ngeneral, what we're asking is what is
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.44,1:16:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the general range of where this is.\NThe calibrated levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:16:48.88,1:16:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,are therefore sort of rough generalities\Nin a way. There is probably a great deal
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.12,1:17:01.84,Default,,0,0,0,,of difference between\N402 and 404. So if we got into m more
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.84,1:17:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,microscopic research,\Nwe could have a whole class of people
Dialogue: 0,1:17:06.56,1:17:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,researching out for a number of years\Nwhat are the differences in every area
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.96,1:17:17.36,Default,,0,0,0,,of life. Love, relationship, earnings,\Nuh your preference for uh TV programs,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:17.36,1:17:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,what channels you watch, which\Ncommentators you prefer, which
Dialogue: 0,1:17:20.15,1:17:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,newspapers you read, what magazines.\NThere's probably quite a lot of
Dialogue: 0,1:17:23.84,1:17:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,difference between 402 and 404. When you\Nlook at it in microscopic analysis,
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.92,1:17:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,annual earnings, the number per thousand\Nof people who have doctorates in that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.80,1:17:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,particular field, etc. So microscopic\Nanalysis is different than the way we're
Dialogue: 0,1:17:39.84,1:17:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,using it. We're looking at generalities,\Nyou know, in what level in what level
Dialogue: 0,1:17:47.19,1:17:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,does that range so that we can get a\Nfeeling and a sense of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:56.00,1:18:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If we calibrate the music we had this\Nmorning in the 700s
Dialogue: 0,1:18:00.80,1:18:06.56,Default,,0,0,0,,then we know you know about it's in the\Nmid 735 738 something. If you're going
Dialogue: 0,1:18:06.56,1:18:12.56,Default,,0,0,0,,to do more microscopic uh analysis which\Nwe occasionally do do uh then one has to
Dialogue: 0,1:18:12.56,1:18:17.28,Default,,0,0,0,,be extremely specific in the way it's\Nlanguaged. one has to be aware of
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.28,1:18:20.71,Default,,0,0,0,,whether you're talking about the memory\Nof it, the sense of it, the feel of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:18:20.71,1:18:26.23,Default,,0,0,0,,the identity of it, the\Nor the uh definition of it etc. So
Dialogue: 0,1:18:26.23,1:18:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,that's much more concentrated,\Nnot suitable for demonstration purposes.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.04,1:18:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to know what does the 700s feel\Nlike? The 700s feels like the music that
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.08,1:18:46.56,Default,,0,0,0,,was played before and we'll play it\Nagain. The 700s feels like Nico's
Dialogue: 0,1:18:46.56,1:18:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,chanting. Nico's chanting calibrates\Naround 740, 750 around there.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:53.28,1:19:08.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what the 700s feel like.\NThat's what they look like.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:08.56,1:19:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,If we want to know if a politician is\Ncoming from
Dialogue: 0,1:19:12.96,1:19:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,honesty or not,\Nwe get, let's say he's at 450, 455. It
Dialogue: 0,1:19:19.52,1:19:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't make any difference whether he's\N452 or 455. You understand? We get that
Dialogue: 0,1:19:23.76,1:19:29.67,Default,,0,0,0,,he's coming from the mid-range of what\Nin our world is accepted as reasonable,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:29.67,1:19:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,logical, provable,\Nethical,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:34.23,1:19:40.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and integrous. Huh?\NSometimes all you really want to know is
Dialogue: 0,1:19:40.96,1:19:46.15,Default,,0,0,0,,whether a thing is over 200 or not.\NThere's lots and lots of spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:19:46.15,1:19:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,books.\NSome of them are frankly quite deranged.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.28,1:19:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But anyway,\Nyou can walk through any bookstore. No,
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.04,1:20:01.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not their book. Your books there. Most\Npeople in the spirituality have
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.76,1:20:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,accumulated tons of books on everything.\NAnd we've mentioned before if you
Dialogue: 0,1:20:06.96,1:20:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,calibrate is whether they're integrous\Nor not. Just do integrous or not. The
Dialogue: 0,1:20:12.71,1:20:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,books that make you go strong and the\Nbooks books that make you go weak
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.60,1:20:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and you put them in two different piles\Nand then you sort of after a week or so
Dialogue: 0,1:20:22.96,1:20:29.28,Default,,0,0,0,,walking around between them you get what\Nis imagination and what is reality. You
Dialogue: 0,1:20:29.28,1:20:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,know,\Nas I say, many of them are convincing.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:35.67,1:20:40.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the main thing you want to know is\Nit over 200 or not. And many people send
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.40,1:20:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,me books they want me to calibrate.\NAnd you know, it's really irrelevant.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:45.04,1:20:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,They're either integrous or they're not\Nintegrous because the only important
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.88,1:20:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,thing about the spiritual pathway is\Nwhether you're on it. Not really
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.80,1:20:57.12,Default,,0,0,0,,important how far you are on it. It's\Nthe fact that you're on it.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:57.12,1:21:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the population hasn't made it\Nout of the water onto the beach yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:03.76,1:21:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?\NHasn't come down out of the trees yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:09.19,1:21:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.\N78% of the population is hasn't even
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.00,1:21:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,gotten to first base yet.\NSee what's important? What's important?
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.48,1:21:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What's important is to cross this line\Nhere at 200. You know what's important
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.00,1:21:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be\Nis to begin to value integrity, to value
Dialogue: 0,1:21:33.76,1:21:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,truth, to value honesty, to value love.\NNow, as incredible as it may sound, I
Dialogue: 0,1:21:44.15,1:21:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,say a great part of the world's\Npopulation cannot decide whether love is
Dialogue: 0,1:21:48.40,1:21:53.04,Default,,0,0,0,,better than hate.\NThere are many countries in which you
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.04,1:22:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,can be executed for lovingness. Do you\Nknow that that it's illegal?
Dialogue: 0,1:22:00.63,1:22:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,To this day,\Ncertainly in Paul Pot's
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.36,1:22:11.44,Default,,0,0,0,,country,\Nany
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.44,1:22:16.23,Default,,0,0,0,,exhibiting any degree of love was\Nconsidered weakness and a crime
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.23,1:22:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,punishable by death.\Na weakness.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:23.28,1:22:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,When it's time to skewer your enemy, if\Nyou hesitate out of mercy, you get you
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.23,1:22:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,get shot in subordination.\NThey have a very clear idea of right and
Dialogue: 0,1:22:35.52,1:22:43.92,Default,,0,0,0,,wrong.\NLove is wrong.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:43.92,1:22:55.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Love is a weakness.\Nwhether peace is better than war.
Dialogue: 0,1:22:55.28,1:23:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Most of the people on the planet would\Nsay no, it's not.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:03.52,1:23:12.63,Default,,0,0,0,,78% of the pe people on the planet\Ndon't want peace at any price.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.63,1:23:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,How do we know that? Because if people\Nwanted peace, they would have it.
Dialogue: 0,1:23:17.44,1:23:24.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Simple.\NIf they said yes to peace, then they
Dialogue: 0,1:23:24.23,1:23:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,would have peace. The fact that we don't\Nhave peace means that most people do not
Dialogue: 0,1:23:28.40,1:23:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,want peace.\NThere's no point of parading in the rain
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.96,1:23:37.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and the snow, folks.\N78% of the people out there having the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:37.52,1:23:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,slightest interest in peace.\NWhy? Because you would have to give up
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.52,1:23:50.63,Default,,0,0,0,,the satisfaction of being right.\NWho's going to give that up?
Dialogue: 0,1:23:50.63,1:23:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Most people would rather die than admit\Nthey were wrong. And they do by the
Dialogue: 0,1:23:57.28,1:24:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,millions. By the millions. By the\Nmillions.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:03.52,1:24:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So the main cause of death is not war.\NWar has got nothing to do with it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.88,1:24:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,War is just the mechanism by which\Nyou've killed yourself by worshiping
Dialogue: 0,1:24:16.63,1:24:21.84,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood instead of truth.\NAnybody can have peace anytime he wants
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.84,1:24:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,it. All he has to do is be willing to\Nsacrifice being right to peace. There
Dialogue: 0,1:24:27.67,1:24:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you go. How long did that take?\NOne second. If the world wanted peace,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.71,1:24:45.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it would have it right now.\NYou can't sell people peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.92,1:24:53.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't have much appeal.\NPeace as a political slogan.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.28,1:25:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,As a reality, people despise it.\NPeople do anything to avoid it.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:00.88,1:25:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,People hate it.\NBrings an end to their dreams.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:09.44,1:25:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,brings an end to their illusions of the\Nsource of their power,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:13.19,1:25:21.19,Default,,0,0,0,,the value of their lifestyle.\NPeace would invalidate most of the
Dialogue: 0,1:25:21.19,1:25:30.40,Default,,0,0,0,,positionalities that holds their whole\Nmind together.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:30.40,1:25:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Winning and gaining, being right,\Nsubverting the truth under distortions
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.04,1:25:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of truth would destroy the whole\Npolitical system.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:46.23,1:25:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Where would you hide?\NWhere would you hide?
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.67,1:25:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If this side is against this and this\Nside is against that and obviously 50%
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.63,1:26:08.40,Default,,0,0,0,,are wrong right to start with. Right?\NSo truth is not something you can vote
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.40,1:26:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for.\NSo the value of integrity in today's
Dialogue: 0,1:26:13.36,1:26:17.44,Default,,0,0,0,,society and those of you in the audience\Nwho are trying to take spiritual
Dialogue: 0,1:26:17.44,1:26:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,principles into business know that\Nintegrity is now becoming the you the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:22.48,1:26:28.23,Default,,0,0,0,,new yard stick.\NThat which is respected that which the
Dialogue: 0,1:26:28.23,1:26:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,world is be is learning is the best\Ninvestment.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:32.96,1:26:38.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The best investment we can make is in\Nthat which is integrous.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:38.63,1:26:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So we invest in our own commitment to\Ntruth.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:43.19,1:26:47.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We ask God for help to overcome the\Nobstacles of which we are aware and
Dialogue: 0,1:26:47.84,1:26:52.23,Default,,0,0,0,,which we are unaware that stand in its\Nway.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.23,1:26:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,And as each one of us chooses\Ntruth over falsehood,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:57.36,1:27:01.92,Default,,0,0,0,,we transform the world into the state of\Npeace.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:01.92,1:27:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,That is how peace comes about.\NIt comes about as the con the automatic
Dialogue: 0,1:27:08.48,1:27:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence of each one of us\Nrejecting falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:16.80,1:27:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,To reject it, you first have to be able\Nto identify it.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:24.00,1:27:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,So in a way the pathway to truth\Ndevotional non-duality is the same as
Dialogue: 0,1:27:28.88,1:27:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,renunciation.\NThose who are committed to enlightenment
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.23,1:27:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,are by definition renunciates.\NYou're renunciates of falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:41.84,1:27:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You're renunciates of idols.\NYou're a renunciate of the
Dialogue: 0,1:27:46.63,1:27:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,gratifications of the temptations of the\Nego.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.36,1:27:57.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So renunciation is an inwardness\Ncommitment.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:57.19,1:28:04.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be symbol uh it can be symbolized\Nby joining a saga. It can be symbolized
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.88,1:28:11.36,Default,,0,0,0,,by joining a monastery.\NIt can be symbolized by dietary
Dialogue: 0,1:28:11.36,1:28:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,regulation and prayers,\Nstyles of haircut, dress, sandals, the
Dialogue: 0,1:28:16.63,1:28:25.12,Default,,0,0,0,,whole deal. Though what they symbolize\Nis your commitment in and of themselves.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:25.12,1:28:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They are meaningless\Nas symbols of what you are committed to.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.48,1:28:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,They're merely a confirmation.\NThe true spiritual devote then is a
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.92,1:28:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,renunciate of all that stands in the way\Nof peace and renounces it because of its
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.71,1:28:53.67,Default,,0,0,0,,falsehood.\NTo be able to see that it's falsehood is
Dialogue: 0,1:28:53.67,1:28:59.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the purpose of the kinesiologic test. So\Nthe purpose of the test is to subserve
Dialogue: 0,1:28:59.28,1:29:04.32,Default,,0,0,0,,the removal of that which is false upon\Nthe planet. And by removing that which
Dialogue: 0,1:29:04.32,1:29:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,is false only the true remains\Nand that which is true is not different
Dialogue: 0,1:29:10.71,1:29:18.63,Default,,0,0,0,,than peace.\NThe way to peace then is to be able to
Dialogue: 0,1:29:18.63,1:29:22.56,Default,,0,0,0,,identify falsehood. Let go your\Nattachment to it even though you're
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.56,1:29:27.84,Default,,0,0,0,,enamored of it\Nand be willing to sacrifice the
Dialogue: 0,1:29:27.84,1:29:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,gratification that you get out of that\Npositionality
Dialogue: 0,1:29:32.08,1:29:43.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and surrender it to God. Therefore, the\Ndevotion is to truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:43.19,1:29:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter what you're attached to, you\Nsay
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.48,1:29:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to thee, oh God, do I deliver this.\NThe choice is always between God
Dialogue: 0,1:29:56.88,1:30:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,or that positionality.\NOut of devotion to God, one is willing
Dialogue: 0,1:30:03.04,1:30:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,to lay down\Nthe gratification and satisfaction of
Dialogue: 0,1:30:07.84,1:30:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that positionality\Nof getting even, being right.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.52,1:30:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,indulging in woe. Indulging in guilt.\NGuilt is egocentric.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:25.60,1:30:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Following in guilt is really\Nself-indulgence.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:30.71,1:30:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's being like a skinny aesthetic with\Nhis hair hanging down to his knees all
Dialogue: 0,1:30:35.60,1:30:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,filthy and dirty.\NThat's an intelligence, folks.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:45.36,1:30:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,getting off on aeticism, right? Oh,\Nno. Bagging bones himself. I know. I've
Dialogue: 0,1:30:51.28,1:30:55.92,Default,,0,0,0,,done it. You go for weeks without\Neating, bathing, shaving, sunshine,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.92,1:31:00.32,Default,,0,0,0,,combing your hair.\NAnd I told you, I think one time I
Dialogue: 0,1:31:00.32,1:31:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,walked right into the wall in that\Nstate. Body just disappeared. I didn't
Dialogue: 0,1:31:04.08,1:31:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,know it was there. And walked around and\Nthere was this person in the mirror.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:07.36,1:31:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,shocked the wits out of me that somebody\Nwas in the house with me.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.71,1:31:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And I I I couldn't understand what that\Nwas. And then I realized, oh, oh yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:17.76,1:31:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And I walked away from it and walked\Nright into the wall. Smack into the
Dialogue: 0,1:31:21.28,1:31:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,wall.\NComplete disidentification with the
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.60,1:31:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,physicality. Huh.\NWell, that doesn't serve the world too
Dialogue: 0,1:31:29.92,1:31:37.04,Default,,0,0,0,,well.\NIt came that that was a
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.04,1:31:42.48,Default,,0,0,0,,self-gratification, a narcissistic\Nself-indulgence and piety.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.48,1:31:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, work in piety for all the\Nspiritual ego you can get out of it,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:46.23,1:31:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,right?\NIt's like looking down on people who
Dialogue: 0,1:31:52.48,1:32:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,aren't humble, right?\NYou're looking down at people who aren't
Dialogue: 0,1:32:03.60,1:32:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual, right? Yeah.
